HEADWORD: Arable
<hw>Ar"a*ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arable</ets>, L. <ets>arabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>arare</ets> to plow,
akin to Gr. <?/, E. <ets>ear</ets>, to plow. See
<er>Earable</er>.]</ety> <def>Fit for plowing or tillage; -- hence,
often applied to land which has been plowed or tilled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arable</ent>⟦br⟧

